$ skopeo inspect docker://docker.io/library/nginx  --raw | shasum -a 256
ed7f815851b5299f616220a63edac69a4cc200e7f536a56e421988da82e44ed8
```

```
$ skopeo inspect --override-os  linux --override-arch  arm  --override-variant v5 docker://docker.io/library/nginx
{
    "Name": "docker.io/library/nginx",
    "Digest": "sha256:ed7f815851b5299f616220a63edac69a4cc200e7f536a56e421988da82e44ed8",
    "RepoTags": [
        ...
    ],
    "Created": "2020-10-13T02:54:50.241053937Z",
    "DockerVersion": "19.03.12",
    "Labels": {
        "maintainer": "NGINX Docker Maintainers \u003cdocker-maint@nginx.com\u003e"
    },
    "Architecture": "arm",
    "Os": "linux",
    "Layers": [
        "sha256:f991c1e1ee2c48f16625b6b61310bf3c0616c0dbda4762019117e86fd29cf9ce",
        "sha256:9e35c110ddfdcec2660c53d68f70748bfef62e6f91af64b4516ccaa4723b1a68",
        "sha256:44d43cd6b4274eeb69ebae957b02e2ce9d316a4c89e227ad6732c1dc9ae54af8",
        "sha256:581afee31c3f56222236b2b31fb67a8c52791ced20fb3be43f4ba88157b8c94f",
        "sha256:2904bf1ef70a8c6d7f743f5964002f18482d79955604447adce10b270aa3fffb"
    ],
    "Env": [
        "PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin",
        "NGINX_VERSION=1.19.3",
        "NJS_VERSION=0.4.4",
        "PKG_RELEASE=1~buster"
    ]
}
```

In the example above notice that the digest reported is for manifest list and not the single arch image with given variant override.  I would expect that if I provide the `--override-os`, `--override-arch` and `--override-variant` flags to `skopeo inspect` that the digest reported for the image would be that of the single arch image matching the overrides, and not that of the manifest list.  

Is this the expected behavior to report the manifest list digest always?
